Final Conclusion

This threat hunt confirmed PwnCrypt ransomware activity on `vme-windows-hun`.

The investigation found multiple files containing the known `.pwncrypt` indicator, showing that important files had been encrypted.

A pivot into process telemetry confirmed that PowerShell was used around the same time as the file encryption activity. The process command line showed execution policy bypass and execution of `pwncrypt.ps1` from `C:\ProgramData`.

The system was immediately isolated to reduce the chance of spread. Because ransomware activity was confirmed, the recommended recovery action was to rebuild or reimage the device.

Additional prevention steps included creating a detection rule, adding `pwncrypt` to a blocklist, and improving monitoring for PowerShell execution policy bypass.

This project demonstrates how known indicators of compromise, file telemetry, process telemetry, and response actions can be combined to quickly identify and contain ransomware activity.
